                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-172-off1060 t18211205-172-crimeloc1062"></join>. On the 6th of December, I missed a shift, which hung in the garden by the back door; my child cried out, "Mother, a man has taken the shift off the line, and is putting it into his hat." I ran out, and saw somebody running up the road. The officer stopped the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-172-person1761">
                  THOMAS 
                  IZARD
               <interp inst="t18211205-172-person1761" type="surname" value="IZARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-172-person1761" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-172-person1761" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 6th of December, I was informed a shift was stolen, and on Crouch-end hill I caught hold of the prisoner, and asked where he was going, he said to Golden-lane; he had the shift tied round him like an apron, quite wet.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-172-person1762">
